Drop NO.1 is almost here!!! figured I’d give a little backstory on Beesh for those who have recently tuned in. I’m Ashley, a mama to one & the owner/founder of Beesh.

This little dream sparked when I had my son in 2017 and as any mom can relate, our bodies change after having a kid. My family and I live in Florida, we spend almost every weekend at the beach and while shopping for new swimwear postpartum if I found swim for myself it was not sexy at all, and did not compliment my curves. I am a firm believer that becoming a mom doesn’t mean you need to completely loose yourself to your children. It’s still okay to look sexy if you want too, and every single one of us deserves to feel like the best damn version of ourselves.

May of 2022 I was answering questions on IG stories, one of you asked what my dream job would be & I answered “to design & own my own swimwear/beach essentials brand”. 

@jennafreire , my friend & founder of Mina Baie responded “Do it. You’d be so good at it.” Which then turned into the two of us partnering together to bring Beesh to life! It’s crazy how life happens. Being such a huge fan of MB and admiring how she created & ran her business I couldn’t think of a more perfect person to mentor me through this whole process and give me the push I needed.

I wanted to create swim that would make us women feel sexy & confident, enhance our curves & overall provide an effortless luxe vibe for days by the water with matching co-ord sets that could take you from the beach to drinks with the girls. 

We offer sizes XS-XXL and will be dropping different styles/color-ways with each launch. We have big plans for the future including kids, men’s, beach essentials, etc. 

I’m SO thankful to every single one of you who have been cheering me along, honestly can’t believe this is really happening & cannot wait for you to get your hands on Beesh!!!
